metadata.ingestion_notes: Each clause must include policy_id and section; store page spans when extracted. Agent must cite policy_id/section in answers.

catalog.title: Code of Conduct & Ethics
catalog.summary: Ethical standards; reporting concerns; no retaliation; non‑discrimination; anti‑harassment; conflict of interest; protection of assets.

faq.q: How do I report a CoC breach?
faq.a: Use manager → HRBP → Whistleblower as per escalation. Sexual harassment goes to ICC/IC as per POSH.

qa.a: You must report via your Manager → HRBP → Whistleblower, or ICC for sexual harassment [POL-COND-001 §2].

qa.q: Can I use company property for personal use?
qa.a: No, misuse of assets is prohibited under Integrity [POL-COND-001 §3.2].

qa.q: How many attendance regularizations are allowed?
qa.a: You may submit 4 regularizations per month within 7 days [POL-FAQ-015 §zing].
Within 45 days of last working day [POL-FAQ-015 §payroll].

catalog.title: Leave Policy
catalog.summary: Calendar leave cycle (Jan–Dec). EL 24 (carry forward 7, encash on exit), Flexi Leave 12–14 (mix of SL/CL/Wellness/Celebratory/Bereavement), Maternity 26 weeks, Paternity 4–7 days, Adoption up to 6 months (age‑based). Apply via HRMS and manager approval.

qa.q: How many EL can I carry forward?
qa.a: You can carry forward up to 7 Earned Leaves [POL-LEAVE-002 §EL].

qa.q: Am I eligible for paternity leave?
qa.a: Yes, 4–7 days of paternity leave are available [POL-LEAVE-002 §PAT].

catalog.title: Employee Meal Policy (Store)
catalog.summary: Store employees: two regular beverages + one food per working day (in‑house consumption only). PT: one beverage + one side (shift‑linked). Store Managers: 30% discount twice a month.

qa.q: What meals are store employees entitled to?
qa.a: Two beverages and one food item per working day [POL-MEAL-012 §1].
Yes, they get one beverage and one side per shift [POL-MEAL-012 §1].

catalog.title: Media Interaction & Communications CoC (Internal Guideline)
catalog.summary: All media queries routed via PR; only designated spokespersons can comment; do not engage without PR; store staff must log media arrivals; reshare only official posts.

qa.q: Can I talk to a journalist about store updates?
qa.a: No, only designated spokespersons may respond. Route all queries to PR [POL-MEDIA-011 §process].

references.pdf: Revised Mobile Phone Usage Policy For Cafe (1).pdf

qa.q: Where should I keep my phone during shifts?
qa.a: Hand it over to MOD in locked status; stored under CCTV [POL-MOB-014 §1].

qa.q: Who can carry a phone during a shift?
qa.a: Only the Store Manager or MOD, for emergencies [POL-MOB-014 §2].

catalog.title: POSH Policy (Internal Committee & Process)
catalog.summary: Defines sexual harassment; scope of workplace incl. virtual; IC composition; complaint filing within 3 months (+3 months extension); inquiry within 90 days; actions during pendency; sanctions on proof; confidentiality and no‑retaliation.

qa.q: What is the complaint filing window?
qa.a: You must file within 3 months of the incident, extendable by another 3 months [POL-POSH-005 §5].

qa.q: How long does an inquiry take?
qa.a: The IC must complete inquiries within 90 days [POL-POSH-005 §11].

catalog.title: Relocation Policy (Store)
catalog.summary: Relocation types: Joining, Versatility (promotion/other), Self‑request, Deputation. Benefits include hotel stay windows, brokerage/settling advance, travel for self/family, household movement via Admin/quotes; clawback if exit <12 months.

qa.q: What happens if I resign within 12 months of relocation?
qa.a: You may be required to return relocation benefits [POL-RELO-013 §benefits].

catalog.title: Domestic & Local Travel Policy (incl. reimbursement)
catalog.summary: Local vs Domestic cut‑off: 80 km. Personal vehicle reimbursement: 2‑wheeler ₹5/km (Exec+), 4‑wheeler ₹10/km (AOM to CxO). Reservations via Admin; economy class; approvals for >₹10k airfare. City categories A/B/C with lodging, meal per diem grid by grade.

references.pdf: Domestic and local travel policy - Store.pdf

qa.q: What is the reimbursement for 2-wheeler travel?
qa.a: ₹5/km for employees of Executive grade and above [POL-TRV-009 §local].

qa.q: Can I book business class flights?
qa.a: No, only economy class is permitted [POL-TRV-009 §reservations].

catalog.title: Working Hours & Overtime
catalog.summary: 9 hours/day incl 1 hour staggered breaks; 4 weekly offs/month on rotation; OT after +30 min; Baristas covered; ASM/SM not covered; Flexi timers normal rates up to 9:30h then 2x.

qa.a: Overtime applies if you work more than 30 minutes beyond your scheduled shift [POL-WH-003 §5].

qa.q: How many weekly offs do I get?
qa.a: Employees are entitled to 4 weekly offs per month on a rotational basis [POL-WH-003 §3].
